gurmukhi: ਅਭਿਮਾਨੁ ੳੁਤਾਰਨ ਦੇਵਤਿਅਾ; ਮਹਿਖਾਸੁਰ ਸੁੰਡ ੳੁਪਾੲਿਅਾ ॥
transliteration: Abhimaan(u) Outaaran Devtaan Mahikhaasur Suaabh Oupaaiaa||
translation: Mahishasura and Sumbh were created for removing the pride of the gods.

gurmukhi: ਜੀਤਿ ਲੲੇ ਤਿਨ ਦੇਵਤੇ; ਤਿਹ ਲੋਕੀ ਰਾਜੁ ਕਮਾੲਿਅਾ ॥
transliteration: Jit(i) Lae Tin Devte Tih Lokoo Raaj(u) Kamaaiaa||
translation: They conquered the gods and ruled over the three worlds.

gurmukhi: ਵੱਡਾ ਬੀਰੁ ਅਖਾੲਿ ਕੈ; ਸਿਰ ੳੁ੍ਨਪਰ ਛਤ੍ਰੁ ਫਿਰਾੲਿਅਾ ॥
transliteration: Vaddaa Boor(u) Akhaae Kai Sir Oupar Chhatr(u) Phiraaiaa||
translation: He was called a great hero and had a canopy moving over his head.

gurmukhi: ਦਿੱਤਾ ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰੁ ਨਿਕਾਲ ਕੈ; ਤਿਨ ਗਿਰ ਕੈਲਾਸੁ ਤਕਾੲਿਅਾ ॥
transliteration: Dittaa Indr(u) Nikaal Kai Tin Gir Kailaas(u) Takaaiaa||
translation: Indra was turned out of his kingdom and he looked towards the Kailash mountain.

gurmukhi: ਡਰਿ ਕੈ ਹੱਥੋ ਦਾਨਵੀ; ਦਿਲ ਅੰਦਰਿ ਤ੍ਰਾਸੁ ਵਧਾੲਿਅਾ ॥
transliteration: Dar(i) Kai Hattho Daanavoo Dil Andar(i) Traas(u) Vadhaaiaa||
translation: Frightened by the demons, the element of fear grew enormously in his heart;
One day Durga came for a bath.

gurmukhi: ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ਬਿਰਥਾ ਸੁਣਾੲੀ; ਅਪਣੇ ਹਾਲ ਦੀ ॥
translation: Indra related to her the story agony:
“The demons have seized from us our kingdom.
“They have proclaimed their authority over all the three worlds.
“They have played musical instruments in their rejoicings in Amaravati, the city of gods.
“All the demons have caused the flight of the gods.

gurmukhi: ਕਿਨੈ ਨ ਜਿੱਤਾ ਜਾੲੀ; ਮਹਖੇ ਦੈਤ ਨੂੰ ॥
transliteration: Kine Na Jittaa Jaaoo Mahakkhe Dait Noon||
translation: “None hath gone and conquered Mahikha, the demon.
